description:
On a day of unseasonable snowfall in Toronto, people gathered in Queen’s Park on Saturday, May 9, to protest against the lockdown restrictions brought in to stem the spread of the coronavirus.

In this video, protesters can be heard cheering outside the Ontario Legislative Building and waving placards that read “fear over real data”, “God reigns supreme” and “freedom or die”, among other messages.
